@subsubsection Torus

@b{Description}

A single-holed ``ring'' torus, also known as an ``anchor ring.''
This is basically a circular cylinder ``bent'' into a donut shape. Partial donuts (``elbows'') are supported.
Partial ``bent'' cylinders are not currently supported.

@noindent @b{Required-input-slots}

@b{:major-radius}

@itemize {}

 @item Number. Distance from center of donut hole to centerline of the torus.

@end itemize

@b{:minor-radius}

@itemize {}

 @item Number. Radius of the bent cylinder making up the torus.

@end itemize

@noindent @b{Optional-input-slots}

@b{:draw-centerline-arc?}

@itemize {}

 @item Boolean. Indicates whether the bent cylinder's centerline arc should be rendered in some renderings.

@end itemize

@b{:end-caps?}

@itemize {}

 @item Boolean. Indicates whether to include end caps for a partial torus in some renderings. Defaults to T.

@end itemize

@b{:number-of-longitudinal-sections}

@itemize {}

 @item Integer. Indicates the number of arcs to be drawn on along ``surface'' of the torus in some wireframe renderings.

@end itemize

@b{:number-of-transverse-sections}

@itemize {}

 @item Integer. Indicates the number of circular cross-sections of the bent cylinder to show in some wireframe renderings.

@end itemize

@noindent @b{Defaulted-input-slots}

@b{:arc}

@itemize {}

 @item Angle in Radians. Indicates the end angle for the donut. Defaults to twice pi for a full-circle donut.

@end itemize

@b{:inner-minor-radius}

@itemize {}

 @item Number. Radius of the inner hollow part of the bent cylinder for a hollow torus. Defaults to NIL for a solid cylinder

@end itemize

@noindent @b{Computed-slots}

@b{:height}

@itemize {}

 @item Number. Z-axis dimension of the reference box. Defaults to zero.

@end itemize

@b{:length}

@itemize {}

 @item Number. Y-axis dimension of the reference box. Defaults to zero.

@end itemize

@b{:width}

@itemize {}

 @item Number. X-axis dimension of the reference box. Defaults to zero.

@end itemize



@noindent @b{Examples}

@smallexample 
@cartouche
  
  (in-package :gdl-user)
  
  (define-object torus-sample (torus)
    :computed-slots
    ((major-radius 150)
     (minor-radius 42)
     (draw-centerline-arc? t)
     (number-of-longitudinal-sections 10)
     (number-of-transverse-sections 10)
     (display-controls (list :color :green-forest-medium)))

    :hidden-objects ((view :type 'base-view
                           :projection-vector (getf *standard-views* :trimetric)
                           :page-width (* 5 72) :page-length (* 5 72)
                           :objects (list self))))
  

  (generate-sample-drawing :objects (make-object 'torus-sample) 
                           :projection-direction :trimetric)
                  
@end cartouche 
@end smallexample

